Sokoto People’s Democratic Party (PDP) governorship candidate, Mallam Ubandoman has congratulated Sokoto Governor Aminu Tambuwal on his emergence as senatorial candidate for Sokoto South. He said Tambuwal’s affirmation as candidate of the district comprising seven local governments of Yabo, Shagari, Tambuwal, Kebbe, Dange/Shuni, Tureta, and Bodinga was well-deserved. Ubandoma also felicitated with Deputy Sokoto Governor Hon. Munir Muhammad Dan’iya for his successful affirmation as senatorial candidate of PDP in Sokoto North. Sokoto North comprises of Sokoto North, Wamakko, Sokoto South, Tangaza, Gudu, Kware, Binji, and Silame Local Governments.   SOKAPU distributes relief materials to IDPs from…     FG to establish anti-trafficking squads in 110 unity schools     Crowd welcomes Tambuwal back to Sokoto   He also greeted Hon Shu’aibu Gwanda Gobir on his affirmation as the senatorial candidate of PDP in the Sokoto East district comprising Gwadabawa, Isa, Sabon Birni, Goronyo, Gada, Illela, Wurno, and Rabah Local Government Areas. Ubandoma stated residents of the three senatorial districts were lucky to have these eminently qualified individuals vying to represent them at the Upper Chamber. He said the candidates have acquired vast knowledge of parliamentary etiquette in their respective political past. He appealed for more cooperation, unity, and understanding among party leaders, requesting more prayers for the 2023 general elections.